<item>
            <title>[QPID-1644] The client should not declare any exchanges starting with &quot;amq.&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-1644</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the JMS client will send a exchange.declare command even if the exchange name starts with &quot;amq.&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
As per the spec &quot;The client MUST NOT attempt to create an exchange starting with &quot;amq.&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Therefore the client needs to do a simple check before sending  any exchange.declare&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12414048">QPID-1644</key>
            <summary>The client should not declare any exchanges starting with &quot;amq.&quot;</summary>
